The applicant is informed that the submitted details have been assessed by relevant consultees and are hereby approved subject to carrying out the development in accordance with the approved details, in relation to Condition 13 (CO2 Reductions) and 19 (Fire Safety Strategy) of planning permission 22/01233/FUL which state:

Condition 13 - Prior to beneficial occupation of the development to which this permission relates, evidence showing that the development has achieved at least a 66% improvement in CO2 emissions versus Part L of the Building Regulations (in line with the submitted Energy Strategy) shall have been submitted to and approved in writing by the local planning authority. Once approved, any measures necessary to meet the targets shall be maintained throughout the lifetime of the development.

Reason: In the interests of sustainability and energy conservation, in accordance with policies CS1, DM3 and DM4 of the LDF Core Strategy 2012.

